oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Paneled door at Cragfont
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Detail of the door between the living room and front hall of Cragfont. Caption on image: "Door between living room and front hall, showing beautiful paneling of doors, white ash floor, and section of original stencil."

The late Georgian style home was built between 1798 and 1802, and was originally home of General James Winchester. It was named after the Rocky Bluff it is located on. Cragfont was occupied by the Winchester family until 1864.
